@startuml
title Viaverse Media Upload / CDN / Moderation — Component Diagram

component "KMP / Next.js Client\nImage/video picker\nUpload progress\nPreview" as Client
component "API Gateway / App BFF\nMedia API facade" as BFF
component "MediaController\nUploadSessionController" as Controller
component "Media Use Cases\nCreateUploadSession\nConfirmUpload\nAttachMedia\nReportMedia" as UseCases
component "Media Policies\ncontext permission\nmime/size limits\nvisibility\nmoderation status" as Policies
component "Ports\nObjectStoragePort\nCdnUrlPort\nModerationPort\nMediaRepo\nOutboxPort" as Ports
database "S3 / Object Storage\noriginals\nthumbnails\ntranscoded variants" as S3
component "CloudFront CDN\npublic assets\nsigned URLs" as CDN
component "moderation-service\nNSFW\nviolence\nabuse/spam" as Moderation
database "PostgreSQL\nmedia_asset\nmedia_derivative\nmedia_report" as DB
component "media-worker\nEXIF strip\nthumbnail\nvideo transcode" as Worker
queue "Kafka / Outbox\nMediaUploaded\nMediaApproved\nMediaRejected" as Kafka

Client --> BFF : HTTPS
BFF --> Controller : REST
Controller --> UseCases : command/query
UseCases --> Policies : validate
Policies --> Ports : ports
Ports --> S3 : presign/read/write
Ports --> CDN : delivery URL
Ports --> Moderation : scan
Ports --> DB : metadata
UseCases --> Worker : async process
Worker --> S3 : process objects
Worker --> Kafka : result events

note bottom
Domain services reference media by mediaId only.
They do not own object keys, binary processing, CDN policy or moderation state.
end note
@enduml
